oc:kn_1921bd2a a oc:Heuristic,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When drafting any customer-facing communication" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Lead with empathy, be direct with bottom-line-up-front, be honest (never overpromise or hide bad news), be specific (concrete details, timelines, names), take ownership ('we' not 'the system'), close every response with a clear next step, and match the customer's energy level." ;
    oc:hasRationale "These core principles ensure every response builds trust, reduces ambiguity, and moves the situation toward resolution." ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_1c9ff7f8 a oc:DesignPrinciple,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When structuring any customer-facing response" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Use this 4-part structure for most customer communications: (1) Acknowledgment/Context 1-2 sentences, (2) Core Message 1-3 paragraphs, (3) Next Steps 1-3 bullets with who/when, (4) Closing 1 sentence reinforcing availability." ;
    oc:hasRationale "A consistent structure ensures the customer feels heard, gets the information they need, knows what happens next, and has an open channel." ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_2a6724ca a oc:Heuristic,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When determining tone for a specific customer" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Adjust tone by relationship stage: New customer (0-3 months) — more formal, extra context, proactive help. Established (3+ months) — warm, collaborative, reference shared history, more direct. Frustrated/escalated — extra empathy, urgency, concrete action plans, shorter feedback loops." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Relationship stage determines how much context and formality is needed; mismatched tone can feel patronizing or dismissive." .

oc:kn_2db27798 a oc:Constraint,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When determining response length by channel" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Length limits: Chat/IM = 1-4 sentences, Support ticket = 1-3 short paragraphs, Email = 3-5 paragraphs max, Escalation = thorough but with headers, Executive = 2-3 paragraphs max and data-driven." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Overly long responses lose the reader; overly short ones feel dismissive. Channel-appropriate length respects the customer's time." ;
    oc:severityLevel "MEDIUM" .

oc:kn_418b07f2 a oc:CodePattern,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When communicating an outage or incident to a customer" ;
    oc:directiveContent """Hi [Name],

I wanted to reach out directly to let you know about an issue affecting
[service/feature] that I know your team relies on.

**What happened:** [Clear, non-technical explanation]
**Impact:** [How it affects them specifically]
**Status:** [investigating / identified / fixing / resolved]
**ETA for resolution:** [Specific time or update cadence]

I'm personally tracking this and will update you as soon as we have a
resolution. You can also check [status page URL] for real-time updates.

I'm sorry for the disruption to your team's work.

[Your name]""" .

oc:kn_44a9a63c a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:Procedure ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When handling situation-specific responses" ;
    oc:directiveContent "For bug reports: acknowledge impact → state issue status → provide workaround → set resolution timeline → commit to regular updates. For escalations: acknowledge severity → take ownership → provide action plan with timeline → identify accountable person → offer meeting. For bad news: be direct (don't bury) → explain reasoning → acknowledge impact → offer alternatives → provide forward path. For declining requests: acknowledge request → be honest about decision → explain why without being dismissive → offer alternatives → leave door open." ;
    oc:stepOrder 2 .

oc:kn_5ac0be3c a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:Procedure ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When executing the full draft-response workflow" ;
    oc:directiveContent "1. Parse input to determine customer, situation type, urgency, channel, relationship stage, and stakeholder level. 2. Research context from email, chat, CRM, support platform, and knowledge base sources. 3. Generate draft with structured format (To, Re, Channel, Tone, body, internal notes). 4. Run 7-point quality checklist. 5. Offer iteration options (tone, length, stakeholder variants, follow-up drafts)." ;
    oc:stepOrder 1 .

oc:kn_6af3695f a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:Prerequisite ;
    oc:directiveContent "Access to relevant data sources (email, chat, CRM, support platform, knowledge base) for context gathering. Not all sources required — use what is available." .

oc:kn_6f035360 a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:OutputFormat ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When generating a draft response" ;
    oc:directiveContent """## Draft Response

**To:** [Customer contact name]
**Re:** [Subject/topic]
**Channel:** [Email / Ticket / Chat]
**Tone:** [Empathetic / Professional / Technical / Celebratory / Candid]

---

[Draft response text]

---

### Notes for You (internal — do not send)
- **Why this approach:** [Rationale]
- **Things to verify:** [Facts to confirm]
- **Risk factors:** [Sensitive elements]
- **Follow-up needed:** [Post-send actions]
- **Escalation note:** [Review needed by]""" ;
    oc:templateVariables "Channel",
        "Customer contact name",
        "Draft response text",
        "Facts to confirm",
        "Post-send actions",
        "Rationale",
        "Review needed by",
        "Sensitive elements",
        "Subject/topic",
        "Tone" .

oc:kn_8f3f2238 a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:RecoveryTactic ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When determining when to follow up with a customer" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Follow-up cadence: Unanswered question = 2-3 business days. Open support issue = daily (critical) or 2-3 days (standard). Post-meeting = within 24h then at deadline. After bad news = 1 week to check impact and sentiment." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Appropriate follow-up timing shows reliability without being pushy; too soon feels pestering, too late feels neglected." .

oc:kn_b7019233 a oc:CodePattern,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When acknowledging a bug report from a customer" ;
    oc:directiveContent """Hi [Name],

Thank you for reporting this — I can see how [specific impact] would be
frustrating for your team.

I've confirmed the issue and escalated it to our engineering team as a
[priority level]. Here's what we know so far:
- [What's happening]
- [What's causing it, if known]
- [Workaround, if available]

I'll update you by [specific date/time] with a resolution timeline.
In the meantime, [workaround details if applicable].

Let me know if you have any questions or if this is impacting you in
other ways I should know about.

Best,
[Your name]""" .

oc:kn_c2393eea a oc:AntiPattern,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When writing any customer-facing response" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Never use corporate jargon or buzzwords, deflect blame to other teams/systems, use passive voice to avoid ownership, include unnecessary caveats, CC people unnecessarily, or use excessive exclamation marks (max one per email)." ;
    oc:hasRationale "These patterns erode trust, signal evasiveness, and make the response feel impersonal or insincere." ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_dff5e7e1 a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:OutputFormat ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When escalating a customer issue internally" ;
    oc:directiveContent """ESCALATION: [Customer Name] — [One-line summary]

Urgency: [Critical / High / Medium]
Customer impact: [What's broken]
History: [Brief background 2-3 sentences]
What I've tried: [Actions taken]
What I need: [Specific help or decision]
Deadline: [Resolution deadline]""" ;
    oc:templateVariables "Customer Name",
        "Customer impact",
        "Deadline",
        "History",
        "One-line summary",
        "Urgency",
        "What I need",
        "What I've tried" .

oc:kn_e8342fec a oc:Constraint,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "Quality check before presenting draft response" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Before presenting any draft, verify: tone matches situation, no unauthorized commitments, no leaked roadmap details, accurate references to prior conversations, clear next steps with ownership, appropriate stakeholder-level language, and appropriate length for the channel." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Sending a response that fails any of these checks can damage the customer relationship or create legal/policy issues." ;
    oc:severityLevel "CRITICAL" .

_:ref_4f77182f3eda3bda a oc:WorkflowStep ;
    dcterms:description "**Match their energy**: If they're frustrated, be empathetic first. If they're excited, be enthusiastic." ;
    oc:blockType "workflow_step" ;
    oc:stepId "step_7" ;
    oc:stepOrder 7 .

_:ref_56167a461181b3f2 a oc:WorkflowStep ;
    dcterms:description "**Be specific**: Use concrete details, timelines, and names — avoid vague language" ;
    oc:blockType "workflow_step" ;
    oc:stepId "step_4" ;
    oc:stepOrder 4 .

_:ref_a1b2a0ded36d077f a oc:WorkflowStep ;
    dcterms:description "**Be honest**: Never overpromise, never mislead, never hide bad news in jargon" ;
    oc:blockType "workflow_step" ;
    oc:stepId "step_3" ;
    oc:stepOrder 3 .

_:ref_b0b5cf4522af5812 a oc:WorkflowStep ;
    dcterms:description "**Lead with empathy**: Acknowledge the customer's situation before jumping to solutions" ;
    oc:blockType "workflow_step" ;
    oc:stepId "step_1" ;
    oc:stepOrder 1 .

_:ref_bba1099f2ff8e860 a oc:WorkflowStep ;
    dcterms:description "**Be direct**: Get to the point — customers are busy. Bottom-line-up-front." ;
    oc:blockType "workflow_step" ;
    oc:stepId "step_2" ;
    oc:stepOrder 2 .

_:ref_cde0ff7e78fe480d a oc:WorkflowStep ;
    dcterms:description "**Own it**: Take responsibility when appropriate. \"We\" not \"the system\" or \"the process\"" ;
    oc:blockType "workflow_step" ;
    oc:stepId "step_5" ;
    oc:stepOrder 5 .

_:ref_f27a8cd944711897 a oc:WorkflowStep ;
    dcterms:description "**Close the loop**: Every response should have a clear next step or call to action" ;
    oc:blockType "workflow_step" ;
    oc:stepId "step_6" ;
    oc:stepOrder 6 .

